A tragic train collision in Los Angeles was caused by a suicidal man, Juan Manuel Alvarez, who parked his Jeep on the tracks.
Alvarez fled the vehicle before impact, leading to a deadly chain reaction.
Despite initial suicide attempts, he changed his mind and was arrested for causing the crash that claimed at least 10 lives.
Alvarez's motive stemmed from personal issues, including a failed marriage.
Authorities expressed anger at the preventable disaster, highlighting the devastating consequences of his actions.
The incident left many injured and raised questions about railway safety measures.
